@lbj_ev_rfk_trigger
title: Los Angeles
on-arrival: lbj_ev_rfk = 1; lbj_unity -= 12; lbj_liberals -= 12; lbj_antiwar -= 5; lbj_approval -= 6; lbj_coup += 6; lbj_paranoia += 10
go-to: lbj_ev_rfk_scene

@lbj_ev_rfk_scene
title: The Ambassador Hotel
new-page: true

Robert Francis Kennedy is shot in the pantry of the Ambassador Hotel in Los Angeles at 12:15 a.m., June 5, 1968. He has just won the California primary.

He dies twenty-six hours later.

You receive the news in the residence. Lady Bird is there. You do not say anything for a long time.

You and Bobby Kennedy have not liked each other for years. This is well documented. The feelings were mutual and specific and rooted in a competition for a man who is now five years dead. None of that is what you feel right now.

What you feel right now is the second political assassination in five years, the second Kennedy, and something underneath the grief that you do not examine directly — a question about what this country is, what it is becoming, whether the violence that took Dallas and Memphis and now Los Angeles is random or whether it has a logic to it that you cannot see from the inside.

You do not say this to anyone.

- @lbj_ev_rfk_address: Address the nation again.
- @lbj_ev_rfk_commission: Create a commission on political violence.

@lbj_ev_rfk_address
title: Again
on-arrival: lbj_unity += 3; lbj_credibility += 2

You address the nation. You are good at this by now. You are tired of being good at this.

You say the words. The country grieves. The country continues.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_ev_rfk_commission
title: Why
on-arrival: lbj_capital -= 6; lbj_unity += 2; lbj_credibility += 3; lbj_coup -= 3

You create the National Commission on the Causes and Prevention of Violence. You ask it to look at everything: political assassination, civil disorder, the culture of violence in American life.

The commission will report back and say, carefully, that the country has a problem it cannot solve quickly. This is accurate and not particularly useful, but it is at least honest.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

